    <text id="B0409T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Chapman writes to Waldo about the case of Sally Taylor, noting that it is now in
                    the hands of William McBush, the constable. The details of the case are not
                    clear from the letter.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-11-10"><abbr expan="November">Nov</abbr> 10 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Waynesboro</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I received yours of the 6 and will just say in Reply that I have <orig reg="done"
                        >dun</orig> all that I can do in Case of <orig reg="Sally">Slly</orig>
                    Taylor vs James Harrison -- I tried the case and gave her it judgement &amp;
                    Etc, for thirty Dollars which was all I could do -- the <orig reg="claim"
                    >Clame</orig> is in the hands of <abbr expan="William">Wm</abbr> McBush C.W.D.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours Truly</salute>
                    <signed>Wm Chapman <abbr expan="Justice of the Peace">JP</abbr></signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">P.S. The Execution of Sally Taylor is in my hands to
                        collect but no property found with which to satisfy the Execution will do my
                        best to make it. Respectfully <abbr expan="yours">yrs</abbr><lb/>Wm McBush
                        C.W.D.</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
